<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3841a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-16T15:00:00-04:00">June 16, 1934—3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>42. Advices from Geneva indicate that Italy is placing obstacles in
                                the way of the putting into effect of the League’s proposal for an
                                embargo on arms and munitions to Bolivia and Paraguay. Please
                                ascertain discreetly and report by telegram the attitude of the
                                Italian Government and the reasons therefor.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>